Norwegian Trade Surplus Falls
Total imports slipped 2.6% in the month to 12.09 billion
kroner from 12.41 billion kroner, while total exports fell
14.7% to 16.66 billion kroner from 19.54 billion kroner a
year earlier.
   Crude oil accounted for 6.66 billion kroner of total
exports in the month, down 17.9% from 8.11 billion kroner in
January 1991. Gas exports fell by 17.6% to 1.36 billion
kroner from 1.65 billion kroner.
   Excluding crude oil and gas, Norwegian exports dropped
11.6% in January to 8.65 billion kroner from 9.78 billion
kroner a year earlier, the agency said.